00:26:07.980 --> 00:26:10.740
how say ye to my soul, flee as a bird to your mountain.

00:26:10.740 --> 00:26:11.860
Have you ever heard anyone say that,

00:26:11.860 --> 00:26:14.780
use the expression, I wish I could just fly away?

00:26:14.780 --> 00:26:16.300
And I'm not talking about Southwest

00:26:16.300 --> 00:26:19.700
and their little catch, you know, marketing tag.

00:26:19.700 --> 00:26:21.020
I'm just talking about people that say,

00:26:21.020 --> 00:26:22.620
I wish I could just fly away.

00:26:22.620 --> 00:26:23.580
I wish I could just get out.

00:26:23.580 --> 00:26:24.660
What do they mean by that?

00:26:24.660 --> 00:26:26.620
I wish I could get out of the situation.

00:26:27.700 --> 00:26:30.540
And here there's some people that are saying to David,

00:26:30.540 --> 00:26:32.260
he says, he asked the question,

00:26:32.500 --> 00:26:35.780
how say ye to my soul, flee as a bird to your mountain.

00:26:35.780 --> 00:26:37.180
Can I tell you this evening

00:26:37.180 --> 00:26:39.540
that there are times in which other people,

00:26:39.540 --> 00:26:41.220
but there are also times in which maybe

00:26:41.220 --> 00:26:44.020
you talk to yourself and say, I wish I could get away.

00:26:45.380 --> 00:26:46.740
You ever talk to yourself?

00:26:47.740 --> 00:26:50.460
Come on, we're not gonna, you know,

00:26:50.460 --> 00:26:52.100
let's take you to the institution or anything

00:26:52.100 --> 00:26:52.980
if you're talking to yourself.

00:26:52.980 --> 00:26:54.900
I'm just, it happens, right?

00:26:54.900 --> 00:26:56.180
You talk to yourself.

00:26:58.580 --> 00:26:59.980
You can get yourself in a lot of trouble

00:26:59.980 --> 00:27:01.740
when you start talking to yourself.

00:27:02.340 --> 00:27:03.660
Start having a pity party.

00:27:04.540 --> 00:27:05.540
I just wanna get out of here.

00:27:05.540 --> 00:27:06.780
I just wanna, no, no, no.

00:27:06.780 --> 00:27:09.060
He says, how are you saying that to me?

00:27:09.060 --> 00:27:14.060
Listen, I have declared, I have put my trust in the Lord.

00:27:14.180 --> 00:27:16.420
So no matter what comes, no matter what happens,

00:27:16.420 --> 00:27:19.100
no matter what circumstance, no matter the difficulty,

00:27:19.100 --> 00:27:21.820
the depth of the difficulty,

00:27:21.820 --> 00:27:24.620
the people and what they're saying,

00:27:24.620 --> 00:27:27.500
no, I have made this decision.

00:27:27.500 --> 00:27:30.460
I have made the deliberate decision

00:27:30.460 --> 00:27:33.900
and I am declaring for others to know

00:27:33.900 --> 00:27:37.940
that in the Lord put I my trust.

00:27:37.940 --> 00:27:38.780
And so in this evening,

00:27:38.780 --> 00:27:40.620
the challenge is really simple for us.

00:27:40.620 --> 00:27:42.380
As I mentioned by way of introduction,

00:27:42.380 --> 00:27:46.380
that though the Psalm has just seven verses,

00:27:46.380 --> 00:27:49.460
that there are many ways in which we'll be challenged

00:27:50.340 --> 00:27:51.980
as we study these seven verses.

00:27:51.980 --> 00:27:54.220
And tonight the challenge is this.

00:27:54.220 --> 00:27:57.260
Can we declare as the psalmist did,

00:27:57.260 --> 00:28:00.020
in the Lord put I my trust?

00:28:00.660 --> 00:28:02.740
That I've made that deliberate decision

00:28:02.740 --> 00:28:05.620
that no matter what comes my way,

00:28:05.620 --> 00:28:07.140
no matter what the circumstances

00:28:07.140 --> 00:28:09.340
and no matter what the other people are saying,

00:28:09.340 --> 00:28:14.260
I have put my trust in the Lord.

00:28:14.260 --> 00:28:15.100
Why?

00:28:15.100 --> 00:28:16.780
Because the Lord is trustworthy,

00:28:16.780 --> 00:28:18.300
because we know his name,

00:28:18.300 --> 00:28:21.220
because we have this book that he gave us,

00:28:21.220 --> 00:28:24.500
the Bible that reveals to us his nature and his character

00:28:24.500 --> 00:28:26.860
and who he is and what he's capable of doing.

00:28:26.860 --> 00:28:29.380
And I say, no, no, no, I'm not trusting in man,

00:28:29.380 --> 00:28:30.700
I'm not trusting in princes,

00:28:30.700 --> 00:28:32.180
I'm not trusting in my sword,

00:28:32.180 --> 00:28:33.740
I'm not trusting in any of these things.

00:28:33.740 --> 00:28:37.780
No, I'm trusting in the Lord

00:28:37.780 --> 00:28:41.300
and I'm gonna put my trust in God.

00:28:41.300 --> 00:28:43.500
And how important it is for God's people

00:28:43.500 --> 00:28:48.500
to stand as David did in the midst of difficulty

00:28:49.580 --> 00:28:53.340
and say in the Lord put I my trust.

00:28:53.340 --> 00:28:54.180
Let's pray together.

00:28:54.180 --> 00:28:55.140
Father, we love you tonight.

00:28:55.140 --> 00:28:56.940
We thank you for loving us.

00:28:56.940 --> 00:28:59.340
God, I pray that you'd help us tonight.

00:29:00.100 --> 00:29:04.500
I know that in a room, a crowd of any size,

00:29:04.500 --> 00:29:06.740
there are difficulties that we face.

00:29:09.380 --> 00:29:11.580
Lord, sometimes those difficulties

00:29:13.100 --> 00:29:15.900
can bring discouragement in our lives,

00:29:15.900 --> 00:29:17.260
can overwhelm us.

00:29:19.300 --> 00:29:21.660
And God, I pray that tonight you would help us

00:29:21.660 --> 00:29:24.900
from this half a verse of scripture

00:29:24.900 --> 00:29:26.620
as we look at Psalm 11 one

00:29:26.620 --> 00:29:29.740
and then coupled with so many other verses

00:29:29.740 --> 00:29:31.740
of scripture tonight.

00:29:31.740 --> 00:29:33.700
Lord, would you help us to be able to declare

00:29:33.700 --> 00:29:37.020
as the psalmist did in the Lord put I my trust.

00:29:38.340 --> 00:29:43.340
Understanding the importance of being actively engaged

00:29:43.940 --> 00:29:45.660
in making that decision.

00:29:47.740 --> 00:29:50.059
Understanding that you are trustworthy.

00:29:51.059 --> 00:29:56.059
And though in our own human frailty,

00:29:57.059 --> 00:30:00.700
we may be tempted to trust in other things.

00:30:00.700 --> 00:30:08.340
things, including ourselves. Lord, I pray tonight that you would help us to put our

00:30:08.340 --> 00:30:14.900
trust in thee. We thank you for the privilege of Wednesday evenings, not only being able

00:30:14.900 --> 00:30:19.700
to study your word, but spend time together as a church family in prayer. And I pray God

00:30:19.700 --> 00:30:24.260
that you'd bless our time of prayer tonight. I pray that you would help us, Lord, to exalt

00:30:24.260 --> 00:30:29.060
and magnify you. Lord, help us to seek you. We thank you that you're a God who hears and

00:30:29.060 --> 00:30:32.740
answers and that you're able to do exceeding abundantly above all that we ask or think.

00:30:32.740 --> 00:30:38.220
We pray that you'd have your will and way, for it's in Christ's name we pray. Amen.

